Data-Table-Formatter

Data::Table::Formatter is a module that simply formats data tables.  It supports a variety of layouts, including ASCII, CSV, Fixed-width, HTML, JSON, LaTeX, TSV, Wiki, XML, and YAML.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Data::Table::Formatter

Additionally, support and documentation is available on the Data::Table::Formatter website:

	http://danne.stayskal.com/software/data-table-formatter

Please direct all bug reports to RT, CPAN's request tracker:

    http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Data-Table-Formatter

To annotate the documentation for this module, visit AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation:

    http://annocpan.org/dist/Data-Table-Formatter

Finally, if you like or dislike this module, please rate it constructively at CPAN Ratings:

    http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Data-Table-Formatter


